        "text": "held in 1 hand",
        "type": "stat_block_section"
      }
    },
    "subtype": "equipment",
    "text": "A maelstromic destabilizer is a whirling gyroscope of burnished bronze and glass. It strengthens the bonds that hold a creature to this world by weakening those same bonds to every other nearby creature. When activated, the destabilizer emits a constant pleasant chime as it spins. For the next minute, the creature holding the gadget gains the listed resistance to spirit damage, while all creatures not immune to spirit damage in a 10-foot emanation gain the listed weakness to spirit damage.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 159,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "uncommon"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
            "aonid": 26,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "Recall Knowledge",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Uncommon",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 11,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 36,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "07336d377bbfcf8d760f34f32f513526",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Consumable",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 454",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 454",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 454,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "An item with this trait can be used only once. Unless stated otherwise, it\u2019s destroyed after activation. Consumable items include alchemical items and magical consumables such as scrolls and talismans. A character can Craft consumable items in batches of four.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "984375da91f3d0abd6b27d241acc7b20",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "consumable",
            "aonid": 36,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "name": "consumable",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Gadget",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 98,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Guns & Gears pg. 233",
              "aonid": 98,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Guns & Gears pg. 233",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Guns & Gears",
            "page": 233,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Gadgets are consumable technological inventions with innovative uses.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 149,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "94858588d7c573ac8c5cda595ef3a931",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Spirit",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 461",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 461",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 461,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Effects with this trait can affect creatures with spiritual essence and might deal spirit damage. A creature with this trait is defined by its spiritual essence. Spirit creatures often lack a material form.",
        "type": "trait"
      }
    ],
